body:
@drcrallen 

> since this floods logs for some folks, does this need to go into 0.10.1?

I think no, since the extraneous logging was introduced in 0.10.0 so it's not a fresh bug for 0.10.1.

I'm not debating debug, I mean can you switch the logic from

```java
if (currentlyProcessing == null) {
// LOTS OF STUFF
} else {
      log.info(
              "Server[%s] skipping doNext() because something is currently loading[%s].",
              basePath,
              currentlyProcessing.getSegmentIdentifier()
      );
    }
```

to 

```java
if (currentlyProcessing != null) {
      log.debug(
              "Server[%s] skipping doNext() because something is currently loading[%s].",
              basePath,
              currentlyProcessing.getSegmentIdentifier()
      );
  return;
}
// LOTS OF STUFF
```
